# /service — Criar Service

## Uso
```
/service [dominio] [metodos]
```

## Fases

### Fase 0 — Reconhecimento
1. Ler services existentes para entender padroes
2. Identificar entidades do dominio
3. Verificar regras de arquitetura em `.claude/rules/`

### Fase 1 — Criar Service

**Principios**:
- Logica de negocio pura (sem I/O direto)
- Injecao de dependencias para repositorios
- Metodos com responsabilidade unica
- Documentacao em cada metodo publico

**Padroes de Metodo**:
| Prefixo | Proposito | Exemplo |
|---------|----------|---------|
| `filter` | Filtragem com early return | `filterActiveUsers(users)` |
| `compute` | Agregacoes, calculos | `computeAverageScore(scores)` |
| `build` | Construir estruturas | `buildUserMap(users)` |
| `find` | Busca por criterio | `findByStatus(items, status)` |
| `get` | Utilitarios, getters | `getDisplayName(user)` |
| `validate` | Validacao de regras | `validateOrder(order)` |
| `transform` | Transformacao de dados | `transformToDTO(entity)` |

### Fase 2 — Testes
- Testar cada metodo publico isoladamente
- Usar factory functions para dados de teste
- Cobrir edge cases: arrays vazios, nulls, limites
- Services sao funcoes puras → testes sem mocks

### Fase 3 — Validacao
- Rodar testes
- Verificar lint

## Checklist
- [ ] Service sem dependencia de framework/HTTP
- [ ] Cada metodo com responsabilidade unica
- [ ] Documentacao nos metodos publicos
- [ ] Testes sem mocks (logica pura)
- [ ] Edge cases cobertos
- [ ] Nomenclatura consistente com padroes do projeto
{{else}}
# /service — Create Service

## Usage
```
/service [domain] [methods]
```

## Phases

### Phase 0 — Reconnaissance
1. Read existing services to understand patterns
2. Identify domain entities
3. Check architecture rules in `.claude/rules/`

### Phase 1 — Create Service

**Principles**:
- Pure business logic (no direct I/O)
- Dependency injection for repositories
- Single-responsibility methods
- Documentation on every public method

**Method Patterns**:
| Prefix | Purpose | Example |
|--------|---------|---------|
| `filter` | Filtering with early return | `filterActiveUsers(users)` |
| `compute` | Aggregations, calculations | `computeAverageScore(scores)` |
| `build` | Build structures | `buildUserMap(users)` |
| `find` | Search by criteria | `findByStatus(items, status)` |
| `get` | Utilities, getters | `getDisplayName(user)` |
| `validate` | Rule validation | `validateOrder(order)` |
| `transform` | Data transformation | `transformToDTO(entity)` |

### Phase 2 — Tests
- Test each public method in isolation
- Use factory functions for test data
- Cover edge cases: empty arrays, nulls, boundaries
- Services are pure functions → tests without mocks

### Phase 3 — Validation
- Run tests
- Check lint

## Checklist
- [ ] Service without framework/HTTP dependency
- [ ] Each method with single responsibility
- [ ] Documentation on public methods
- [ ] Tests without mocks (pure logic)
- [ ] Edge cases covered
- [ ] Naming consistent with project patterns
{{/if}}
